HEADWORD: Nympholepsy
<hw>Nym"pho*lep`sy</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧m"f⟦osl⟧*l⟦ecr⟧p`s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>ny`mfh</grk> a nymph +
<grk>lamba`nein</grk> to seize.]</ety> <def>A species of demoniac
enthusiasm or possession coming upon one who had accidentally looked
upon a nymph; ecstasy.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>De
Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>nympholepsy</qex> of some fond despair.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nympholeptic</ent>⟦br⟧
